      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll replace the nested loop with a single loop using the formula for summing arithmetic progressions to achieve O(n) complexity instead of O(n²).\nThis approach calculates the total sum in linear time, ensuring it runs well under the 0.5-second limit for N up to 10^6.\nThe code below implements this optimized logic directly.\n\n```python\ndef heavy_sum(n):\n    MOD = 123\n    total = 0\n    for i in range(n):\n        # Sum of (i*j) for j in 0..i-1 is i * (i-1) * i / 2\n        # We compute this modulo MOD at each step to prevent overflow and keep it fast\n        term = (i * (i - 1) * i) // 2\n        total = (total + (term % MOD)) % MOD\n    return total\n```",
